abstract: In its annual stress tests, the Fed looked at how America’s 33 largest banks would do in a recession with sustained high unemployment and negative interest rates.
snippet: In its annual stress tests, the Fed looked at how America’s 33 largest banks would do in a recession with sustained high unemployment and negative interest rates.
lead_paragraph: The nation’s biggest banks have all built up big enough buffers to weather a severe recession in decent shape, United States regulators said on Thursday.

abstract: In the 1970s, Mr. Rohatyn, an investment banker, engineered the rescues first of the New York Stock Exchange and then of the city itself, which was on the verge of financial collapse.
snippet: In the 1970s, Mr. Rohatyn, an investment banker, engineered the rescues first of the New York Stock Exchange and then of the city itself, which was on the verge of financial collapse.
lead_paragraph: If there is ever a Mount Rushmore created for New Yorkers, the faces on it might reasonably be those of Peter Stuyvesant, Fiorello H. La Guardia, Robert Moses and Felix G. Rohatyn.

abstract: A criminal complaint alleges gross bribery to Brooklyn police precinct commanders by two businessmen who became big donors to a group allied with Mayor Bill de Blasio.
snippet: A criminal complaint alleges gross bribery to Brooklyn police precinct commanders by two businessmen who became big donors to a group allied with Mayor Bill de Blasio.
lead_paragraph: New York, like most places of human habitation, has a long history of bribery, but until now the literature did not reveal any documented episodes in which the graft was packaged as Christmas presents and delivered by two Orthodox Jewish businessmen dressed up as elves.

abstract: Inside the identity crisis roiling the Republican Party.
snippet: Inside the identity crisis roiling the Republican Party.
lead_paragraph: Every week or so during the spring, I met with Reince Priebus, the chairman of the Republican National Committee, at the party headquarters on Capitol Hill. We fell into a familiar routine. I would enter his office, usually chaperoned by Sean Spicer, the R.N.C.’s chief strategist and head of communications. Priebus has a healthy appreciation for gallows humor, which is not a bad thing for an R.N.C. chairman these days. “I haven’t started pouring Baileys in my cereal yet,” he says often enough that it has become a signature line. I would regularly break the ice with something sarcastic, like asking Priebus how his party’s Hispanic outreach program was going on the morning after the committee’s head of Hispanic outreach resigned rather than work another day for Donald Trump’s election. “The scent of party unity is in the air,” I said in May when Paul Ryan reported that he was “not there yet” on supporting Trump. “No, that’s incense,” Priebus said, pointing out that he had been burning some behind his desk.

abstract: Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo said “it was probably the most successful session in modern history,” despite falling short on proposals involving ethics and housing reform.

lead_paragraph: ALBANY — It was mid-January when Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo took to the stage here and delivered his vision of the coming legislative year, unveiling a laundry list of nearly 150 proposals.

abstract: The one-year extension of control over New York schools follows a protracted battle in the Legislature, and is a much shorter term than what the mayor had requested.

abstract: “The Underpants,” the comedian’s adaptation of a German farce, shows a sweet young housewife struggling with lust in 1910.
snippet: “The Underpants,” the comedian’s adaptation of a German farce, shows a sweet young housewife struggling with lust in 1910.
lead_paragraph: A German flag with a barely noticeable strip of lace added to its bottom serves as a stage curtain at the beginning of “The Underpants,” a comedy adapted by Steve Martin from a German farce by Carl Sternheim, at Guild Hall in East Hampton.
